race.comment: RHIA (9) on top. She's a lightly raced mare who has always promised a bit, resuming with a soft victory at Mornington in a 0-62, settling midfield and coming away to win by 1.75 lengths in fine style. She sets up nicely here from the low gate and has found another suitable race. HOLLYWOODBOULEVARD (8) resumes having put two wins on the bounce last time in. This is a new test and the draw isn't ideal but watch the betting. KYLE (3) found the line strongly in town first up and a repeat of that sees him hard to beat. BOLD RESPONSE (5) doesn't win out of turn but puts himself up on speed. Back to 1100m should suit and expect to see the 4kg claimer try to run them into the ground.
